evaluation.response:
Guilt is a sly companion, isn't it? Sometimes, even when you think you're enjoying a moment as out of place as this one, these feelings will surface and seems very out of place. But that's okay to acknowledge them. You don't have to push them down or try to force them away. Instead, allow yourself to embrace them as part of your experience in the precious moment you are in.

Guilt can be really specifically related to certain social roles or emotional experiences you may have. It might be helpful to have a conversation with the people around you to clear up any glaring misconceptions or areas of miscommunication that are strenuous on your mental health&#x20;

You are human, and it's okay to have strong emotions. Imagine yourself breathing in and out, allowing you just acknowledge these emotions without judgment, and letting them themselves pass - again without judgment or judgment of yourself for having them.
